data.text:
Animal Crossing: New Horizons (ACNH) Guides

Sea Creatures List Guide: Months, Hours, Sell Prices, Shadows

Sea Creatures are a new type of critter to catch on your island in Animal Crossing: New Horizons for collecting in your Critterpedia, donating to the Museum, and selling for Bells! Learn how to find every Sea Creature including months, hours, shadows, and sell prices in this guide.

They were introduced in the just released Summer Update on July 3rd, 2020 including new features like Swimming, Sea Creatures, Pascal, Pirate Gulliver, and more.

Complete Sea Creatures List in Animal Crossing: New Horizons

There are 40 different Sea Creatures to catch and collect in total in Animal Crossing: New Horizons, which is an increase of +10 from the previous game Animal Crossing: New Leaf!

Find the complete details of appearance months for both the Northern Hemisphere & Southern Hemisphere, hours of availability, shadow size, movement speed, and Bells sell price for each Sea Creature below. This list is ordered by Critterpedia order, top to bottom then left to right.

If you prefer a table format of Sea Creatures to sort by size, speed, or sell price, scroll to the end of this section for a list in table form instead.

Find Pearls In The Ocean While Diving

In addition to the Sea Creatures above, you can also find the Pearl item in the ocean while diving, which is used in Pascal’s Mermaid Set crafting recipes. While it’s found in the ocean, the Pearl does not technically count as a Sea Creature as it cannot be donated to the Museum or collected in the Critterpedia.

However, the Pearl shouldn’t be overlooked as it is an important crafting material to make Mermaid Set furniture items and can be sold for a hefty 10,000 Bells each! Check out our full guide to getting Pearls here.

How To Catch Sea Creatures By Diving

Exclusively found deep under the sea in your island’s surrounding ocean, you must go swimming and dive into the water in order to find and catch these special Sea Creatures. A Wet Suit item is required to go swimming.

You’ll be able to spot Sea Creatures in the ocean by looking out for suspicious bubbles floating up from an area while swimming. When you see these bubbles over an area, press the Y button to begin diving deep into the water and swim towards any shadows — they look just like the fish shadows you’re used to!

After chasing down a sea creature shadow, you’ll catch the critter which can either be donated to the Museum or sold at Nook’s Cranny to Timmy & Tommy for Bells.

Donate Sea Creatures To The Museum

Just as with Fish and Bugs, you’ll want to donate these Sea Creatures to your island’s Museum the first time you catch them. You can find Sea Creatures cataloged in your NookPhone’s Critterpedia as well, including whether they have already been donated or not.
